                    <div class="help-module-header">
                        <div class="help-module-icon" style="background:#f0fdf4;color:#16a34a;"><i class="bi bi-collection"></i></div>
                        <div>
                            <h3>Master Data</h3>
                            <span class="text-muted" style="font-size:.78rem;">Configure foundational data for the application</span>
                        </div>
                        <span class="module-badge">Admin Only</span>
                    </div>
                    <p>Master Data pages are where you configure the foundational data that powers the rest of the application. Set up products, rates, parties, bank accounts, payment modes, and more before using the transactional modules.</p>
                    <ol class="help-steps">
                        <li><strong>Employee Department</strong> — Define organizational departments (used for user management and expense routing).</li>
                        <li><strong>Employee Designation</strong> — Manage job titles and positions.</li>
                        <li><strong>Financial Year</strong> — Configure financial year periods (e.g., 2025-26). The system auto-detects and marks the current FY as active.</li>
                        <li><strong>Expense Category</strong> — Set up categories like Travel, Food, Office Supplies, etc. for expense classification.</li>
                        <li><strong>Product Master</strong> — Manage your product catalog with product types (Healthcare, Hospitality) and descriptions.</li>
                        <li><strong>Product Rate List</strong> — Define pricing for each product: pricing model (Subscription / One-Time), billing frequency (Monthly, Quarterly, Half-Yearly, Annual), and amount.</li>
                        <li><strong>Product Rate Discounts</strong> — Configure discount offers: percentage-based or flat amount discounts for promotions.</li>
                        <li><strong>Party Master</strong> — Manage client/vendor party records used in quotations and invoices.</li>
                        <li><strong>Bank Master</strong> — Record your bank account details for payment processing.</li>
                        <li><strong>Payment Modes</strong> — Configure accepted payment methods (Cash, Bank Transfer, UPI, Cheque, etc.).</li>
                        <li><strong>Terms & Conditions Templates</strong> — Create reusable T&C text blocks that can be attached to quotations and invoices.</li>
                    </ol>

                    <div class="help-tip">
                        <i class="bi bi-lightbulb-fill"></i>
                        <div><strong>Tip:</strong> Set up Master Data in this order for the best experience: Financial Year → Departments → Products → Rates → Parties → Bank → Payment Modes → T&C Templates.</div>
                    </div>
                </div>

                @* ─── EMAIL ENGINE ───────────────────────── *@
                <div class="help-module" id="module-email" data-keywords="email smtp configuration template log notification send engine">
                    <div class="help-module-header">
                        <div class="help-module-icon" style="background:#ecfeff;color:#0891b2;"><i class="bi bi-send-check"></i></div>
                        <div>
                            <h3>Email Engine</h3>
                            <span class="text-muted" style="font-size:.78rem;">SMTP configuration, templates, and delivery logs</span>
